		<profileDesc>
			<abstract>
				<p>We propose a non-linear generative model for human motion data that uses an undirected model with binary latent variables and real-valued &quot;visible&quot; variables that represent joint angles. The latent and visible variables at each time step receive directed connections from the visible variables at the last few time-steps. Such an architecture makes on-line inference efficient and allows us to use a simple approximate learning procedure. After training, the model finds a single set of parameters that simultaneously capture several different kinds of motion. We demonstrate the power of our approach by synthesizing various motion sequences and by performing on-line filling in of data lost during motion capture.</p>
			</abstract>
